  <compounddef id="confhooks" kind="page">
    <compoundname>confhooks</compoundname>
    <title>Hooks in configuration files</title>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The hook extension in the ALSA library allows expansion of configuration nodes at run-time. The existence of a hook is determined by the presence of a @hooks compound node.</para><para>This example defines a hook which loads two configuration files at the beginning:</para><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">@hooks<sp/>[</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>func<sp/>load</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>files<sp/>[</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>&quot;/etc/asound.conf&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>&quot;~/.asoundrc&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>]</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>errors<sp/>false</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>}</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">]</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para><sect1 id="confhooks_1confhooks_ref">
<title>Function reference</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>The function load - <computeroutput><ref refid="conf_8c_1a4008d77ad63047366463350b7726a5ec" kindref="member">snd_config_hook_load()</ref></computeroutput> - loads and parses the given configuration files. </para></listitem>
<listitem>
<para>The function load_for_all_cards - <computeroutput><ref refid="conf_8c_1ac64a8c73293ee35ed3f3958d47bdc721" kindref="member">snd_config_hook_load_for_all_cards()</ref></computeroutput> - loads and parses the given configuration files for each installed sound card. The driver name (the type of the sound card) is passed in the private configuration node. </para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para></sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
  </compounddef>
</doxygen>
